South Korea was rocked by corruption scandals, with Roh calling for an investigation into illegal wiretapping.
The NIS was asked to probe illicit funds donated by a Samsung executive to politicians.
Amid pressure, South Korea's envoy to the US resigned over involvement in a slush fund scandal.
Hong, suspected of being a Samsung intermediary, faced calls to step down.
The NIS apologized for wiretapping, continuing after Kim Dae-jung's presidency.
Roh sought clarity on the scandal, while Samsung issued an apology.
The situation highlighted political corruption and strained relations with North Korea.
